#### **Day 32: HTML Forms and Input Handling**
```markdown
# Day 32: Creating Interactive Forms

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. The `<form>` tag and its attributes (`action`, `method`).
2. Input types: `text`, `password`, `email`, `date`, `radio`.
3. The `<label>` tag for accessibility.
4. Buttons and form submission.

**Learning Summary:**
Forms are crucial because this is how users send data to our Java backend. I learned about the `name` attribute in input tagsâ€”this acts as the key when data is sent to the server (e.g., Spring Boot controller). I also learned the difference between `GET` (data in URL) and `POST` (secure data transfer) methods.

**Code Snippet:**
```html
<h2>Registration Form</h2>
<form action="/submit-data" method="POST">
    <div>
        <label for="username">Username:</label>
        <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
    </div>

    <div>
        <label for="pwd">Password:</label>
        <input type="password" id="pwd" name="password" minlength="8">
    </div>

    <div>
        <p>Gender:</p>
        <input type="radio" id="male" name="gender" value="male">
        <label for="male">Male</label>
        <input type="radio" id="female" name="gender" value="female">
        <label for="female">Female</label>
    </div>

    <button type="submit">Register</button>
</form>
